abstract: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
snippet: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — As excellent as the Bernie Sanders event was — as excellent as it was to hear from the filmmaker Michael Moore and to eat Ben & Jerry’s ice cream scooped by the actual Ben and the actual Jerry, longtime Sanders supporters — it would have been even more excellent, was the general feeling, if Mr. Sanders himself had been able to come to Ottumwa.

abstract: Civil rights activists and black community leaders in Minneapolis continue to call for her to suspend her campaign.
snippet: Civil rights activists and black community leaders in Minneapolis continue to call for her to suspend her campaign.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF — Senator Amy Klobuchar again called for any new evidence to be released in a 2002 murder case that was prosecuted while she was a county attorney, as civil rights activists and black community leaders in Minneapolis continued to call for her to suspend her campaign after a report raised questions about whether a black teenager was wrongly convicted.
headline_main: Klobuchar discusses 2002 case that put black teenager behind bars for life.

snippet: Senator Amy Klobuchar summed up her final pitch with a geographic appeal.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF — In her first event back in Iowa after spending most of the week tethered to Washington for the impeachment trial, Senator Amy Klobuchar summed up her final pitch with a geographic appeal: the path to a Democratic victory in 2020 is through the Midwest.

headline_main: Klobuchar claims path to the White House is through the Midwest.

abstract: “I’ve got the endorsement of every single major newspaper in New Hampshire that has put out an endorsement,” she said.
snippet: “I’ve got the endorsement of every single major newspaper in New Hampshire that has put out an endorsement,” she said.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF — An overflow crowd in a bike shop greeted Senator Amy Klobuchar Saturday morning on the first day of her jetsetting trip around Iowa, powered by a chartered plane to get to the four corners of the state.
headline_main: Klobuchar urges Iowans to look past the caucuses.
